author: Jeff Gluck, USA TODAY Sports
title: Dover qualifying rained out; Kenseth on pole
text:
Dover qualifying rained out; Kenseth on pole USA Today Sports 10 hrs ago by Jeff Gluck, USA TODAY Sports Â© Jasen Vinlove, USA TODAY Sports Jasen Vinlove, USA TODAY Sports DOVER, Del. -- Kevin Harvick's hopes for a season-saving win are off to a bad start at Dover International Speedway.
AdChoices Persistent rain washed out Sprint Cup Series qualifying on Friday, meaning NASCAR will set the starting lineup for Sunday's AAA 400 based on owner points.
That puts all 16 Chase for the Sprint Cup drivers up front, and Harvick -- the pre-playoff favorite who must win in order to advance -- will start 15th based on his position in the points.
Matt Kenseth and Denny Hamlin, who have won the first two races in the Chase, will start on the front row. They'll be followed by Carl Edwards, their Joe Gibbs Racing teammate, and Team Penske's Joey Logano.
All-time Dover winner Jimmie Johnson, who has 10 victories at the 1-mile concrete track, will start fifth. Ryan Newman, Kurt Busch, Brad Keselowski, Martin Truex Jr. and Jeff Gordon -- making his final Dover appearance -- round out the top 10.
Jamie McMurray and Dale Earnhardt Jr., barely hanging onto Chase berths heading into the Dover elimination race, will start 11th and 12th. Then it's Kyle Busch, Paul Menard, Kevin Harvick and Clint Bowyer -- all of who are on the outside of the playoff looking in.
Tony Stewart, who announced his intention to retire following the conclusion of next season, will start 25th.
No drivers failed to qualify, as only 43 teams were entered in the race.
